-- Raiffeisen’s Romanian Units May Get 50 Million-Euro EIB Credits
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2012-01-13T07:28:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/raiffeisen-s-romanian-units-may-get-50-million-euro-eib-credits.html
Raiffeisen International Bank AG (RBI) ’s
Romanian bank and leasing unit may get credit lines amounting to
50 million euros ($64 million) from the  European Investment Bank 
to finance small and medium-sized companies.  Raiffeisen Bank Romania SA may get as much as 35 million
euros, while Raiffeisen Leasing IFN SA may receive as much as 15
million euros in multi-purpose credit lines, EIB said in a
 statement on its website  on Jan. 11. The credit lines are under
EIB appraisal, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  